    <stitle>RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - MXT - RADIATOR and Component INSTALLation - FRONT CROSSMEMBER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FRONT CROSSMEMBER</title>
        <para>Locate the front crossmember assembly for installation prior to re-installing the hood and grille
            assembly. Figure 31 shows some components after re-installation.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Re-connect the 2 horns.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Re-connect the wire harness(es).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Re-attach the hood, hood stabilizing wires and hood tension rods. Refer to Service Manual
                S09013, Hood, Grille, Bumpers and Fender Extensions, for installation of the hood and grille assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201931" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201931.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="484px"
                     scalefitheight="392px"/>
            <caption>Figure 31. Under-Hood View of Some Properly Installed Components on the MXT Vehicle</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
